text: are you looking for a really really easy
dessert to make this holiday season I
have a dessert for you it's another
recipe from my easier than pie no roll
dessert story that I did in November
it's a cranberry cobbler
you don't even need a mixer for this one
it only takes 10 minutes put together 25
minutes in the oven and you have a warm
delicious holiday themed dessert the
first thing that you need to do is
butter a 10-inch cast-iron skillet I
guess you could use a different kind of
skillet but I don't like nonstick
skillet and cast-iron skillets are
naturally nonstick so get the best of
both worlds set that aside
pre-heat your oven to 350 degrees and
whisk together your dry ingredients 1
cup of all-purpose flour a little bit of
leavener a little bit of levity 1 and
1/4 teaspoons of baking powder 1/2 a
teaspoon of fine salt to that add 3/4 of
a cup of sugar whisk it up
time for your wet ingredients 1/2 a cup
of milk 1 large egg you should just
whisk everything together in a liquid
measuring cup it makes it easier to
combine everything in the end and then 6
tablespoons of melted unsalted butter
just whisk those wet ingredients into
the dry ingredients and your batter is
done I'm not kidding it really took less
than 5 minutes
don't you love something that comes
together this quickly and you can serve
it as a holiday dessert scrape your
batter into your prepared pan spread it
evenly over the bottom let it aside for
one sec look at the cranberries ready
you need one and a quarter cups of fresh
cranberries and then just pick through
them and make sure there aren't any soft
ones there at there usually are a couple
hiding in there then add two tablespoons
of sugar to this cranberries are pretty
tart so you want to give them a fighting
chance
plus the sugar makes the top of the cake
nice and golden brown it's win-win
tuition and then you just pour this
right over the top of your batter or I'd
like to spread them out nice and evenly
you don't want them to concentrate it in
the center otherwise the cake will not
bake evenly even distribution of wealth
350 degrees for 25 to 30 after 25
minutes give it a check make sure it
springs back when you touch it lightly
on the top side it's beautiful and
golden brown this is spring back yes it
does that means it's done what do you
think was so easy in so fast zero
rolling involved and good enough for
company if you ask me
